“It is time to allow those doctors and nurses to return to work.
However, it must be done in ways to ensure that we will be able to treat COVID-19 patients,” he added.
Abbott said officials will provide revised plans, outlining the next steps the state will take to reopen, on April 27.
It, the governor said, is all part of the phased strategy to open Texas in a “safe way.”The revised plans will emphasize protecting the most vulnerable while allowing residents to increase interactions, he added.
We can adopt safe strategies that prevent the spread of COVID 19, and step by step, we will open Texas,” Abbott said.